
Sessions/tokens securely managed: NO
Token is stored in localStorage in UserService.ts (line 24), and the JWT secret in application.properties (line 10) is a placeholder string.

All actions properly validated: NO
Some are validated well via DTO annotations, e.g. RegisterRequest.java (line 1), PostRequest.java (line 1). But not all: ToggleLikeRequest.java (line 1) is empty, ReportAdminRequest.java (line 1) has no bean validation annotations.

Media upload/storage secure: NO
There is MIME allowlisting in MediaStorageService.java (line 1), but it trusts contentType, writes directly to a public uploads folder, and has no deeper file validation/scanning.


All input sanitized against SQL injection/XSS: NO
JPA reduces SQL injection risk, but there is no explicit sanitization/escaping layer for all user content on the backend.


All actions confirmed with visual feedback: NO
Reporting/deleting/admin actions do, but like/subscribe/comment are not consistently confirmed with dialogs or success feedback.




Uploaded files retrievable without corruption: NO
Retrieval path exists via WebConfig.java (line 15), but I could not verify this at runtime.
